ope disc (Politeness)", "work_id": 120075, "role": "publisher", "role_id": 942, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3092213, "title": "Phenakistiscope disc (Man pumping water)", "work_id": 120076, "role": "publisher", "role_id": 942, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "1788", "date_of_death": "1875", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "Thomas McLean (1788 - 1875) was a print seller and publisher from London.\n\nMcLean specialized in the publication of political caricatures. His works were published in journals such as the Monthly Sheet of Caricatures.\n\nHe was a respected dealer of art and print and annually held exhibitions for watercolor and oil paintings. He also supported young, but not well-known artists.\n\nHis business was located on Haymarket Street in London. After his death in 1875, the business was taken over by his son, Thomas Miller McLean.", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2025-03-19T22:40:02.086505+11:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "ae74b5ad-546e-41f9-a552-6da958ba4bd0", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "39440", "external_references": [{"id": 33365, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q121315250"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-19T22:40:02.086765+11:00"}, {"id": 71444, "name": "Superlectron", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2681303, "title": "TV Challenger Series 3000", "work_id": 100284, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-08-14T12:01:38.705271+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "496c641e-4b8f-4d7a-98d0-30481b1a1a75", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "39381", "external_references": [], "date_modified": "2025-03-07T01:17:04.105